      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Absolute hemolysis index is the direct regulatory QoI; model output maps directly to clinical threshold without post-processing surrogates.",
      "rationale": "The model outputs normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) which is the regulatory QoI. However, the damage accumulation model was calibrated on a different pump geometry, introducing a surrogate step. QoI relevance is partial."
    },
    {
